<abstract><t>Hierarchical Service Function Chaining (hSFC) is a network architecture allowing an organization to compartmentalize a large- scale network into multiple domains of administration.  The goals of hSFC are to make a large-scale network easier to reason about, simpler to control and to able support independent functional groups within large operators.</t></abstract>

